# API (`apps/api`)

ASP.NET Core 10 Web-API, **EF Core**, **SQL Server**. JSON-Enums als **camelCase** (`JsonStringEnumConverter`). **Domänenregeln:** [`.cursor/PROJECT_MEMORY.md`](.cursor/PROJECT_MEMORY.md).

## Pflege

**Nach neuen Controllern, Endpoints, Entities oder Migrationen:** diese Regel **aktualisieren** (inkl. Web-Client [`apps/web/lib/api.ts`](apps/web/lib/api.ts), falls sich Pfade ändern).

## Tech & Befehle

- **Lokal:** `cd apps/api` → `dotnet run` (Port laut Launch/Output, oft **5112**; Health: `GET /health`)
- **Build:** `dotnet build` aus Solution/Projekt
- **EF:** `dotnet ef database update` / `dotnet ef migrations add Name` (Tool: `dotnet-ef`)
- **Migration + Seed:** In **Development** in [`Program.cs`](apps/api/Program.cs): `MigrateAsync()` + `DevelopmentSeeder.SeedAsync`

## Konfiguration

- **Connection String:** `ConnectionStrings:DefaultConnection` (siehe `appsettings*.json`, Docker: `docker-compose.yml` → `ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection`)
- **CORS:** `AllowedOrigins` (Default u. a. `http://localhost:3000`) – [`Program.cs`](apps/api/Program.cs)
- **Swagger:** nur in Development aktiv

## Ordner (überblick)

| Ordner | Inhalt |
|--------|--------|
| [`Controllers/`](apps/api/Controllers/) | REST: `Companies`, `Contacts`, `TimelineEntries`, `Search` – Routen `[Route("api/[controller]")]` |
| [`Entities/`](apps/api/Entities/) | `Company`, `Contact`, `TimelineEntry` |
| [`Contracts/`](apps/api/Contracts/) | Request/Response-DTOs (`*Dtos.cs`) |
| [`Enums/`](apps/api/Enums/) | u. a. `CompanyStatus`, `TimelineEntryType`, `TimelineSource` |
| [`Data/`](apps/api/Data/) | `ValentinRsmDbContext`, `Migrations/`, `DevelopmentSeeder.cs` |

## REST-Überblick (mit Web-Client abgleichen)

| Ressource | Controller | Typische Pfade (Client nutzt Kleinbuchstaben) |
|-----------|------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| Firmen | `CompaniesController` | `GET/POST /api/companies`, `GET/PUT/DELETE /api/companies/{id}` |
| Kontakte | `ContactsController` | `GET /api/contacts?companyId=…`, `GET/POST`, `GET/PUT/DELETE /api/contacts/{id}` |
| Timeline | `TimelineEntriesController` | `GET /api/timelineentries?…`, `POST`, `POST/PUT/DELETE …/{id}` |
| Suche | `SearchController` | `GET /api/search?q=…` |

**Hinweis:** ASP.NET-Routing ist **case-insensitive**; das Frontend spricht z. B. `/api/timelineentries` an.

## Konventionen

- **Cascade:** Löschverhalten von Firmen/Kontakten/Timeline konsistent mit DB und DTOs halten.
- **Neue Endpoints:** DTOs in `Contracts/`, Mapping in Controller, ggf. Migration, **Frontend** `lib/api.ts` erweitern.
